Lumpy skin disease, Serbia
--------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 1 Jul 2016 from Dr Budimir Plavšić, Head, Animal Health Department Veterinary Directorate, Ministry of Agriculture and Environmental Protection, Belgrade, Serbia

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 3
Date of start of the event: 4 Jun 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 7 Jun 2016
Date submitted to OIE: 1 Jul 2016
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: Lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (25)

[For the detailed locations, epidemiological statistics and a map pertaining to each of the 25 new outbreaks (of which 22 are located in the district Pcinjski, 2 in the district Jablanicki and one in Pirotski), please refer to the source URL. - Mod.AS]

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 25
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 151 / 29 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics (rates apparent, expressed in percentages)
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 19.21 / 0.00 / 0.00 / 0.00
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive; vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; stamping out; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; zoning; control of vectors; no treatment of affected animals
Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated
Serbia / Cattle / 41 387

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Veterinary Institute (VSI), Kraljevo (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / real-time PCR / 30 Jun 2016 / Positive

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Since the start of the lumpy skin disease (LSD) event in Serbia on 4 Jun 2016, initially in a backyard farm in Ljiljance village, Bujanovac municipality, Pcinja district, a total of 82 outbreaks have been reported in 4 south-eastern provinces. The following epidemiological data, as of 1 Jul 2016, have been derived from OIE's archived "outbreak summary":

Total outbreaks = 82 (Submitted)
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 530 / 91 / 0 / 83 / 0

According to media, vaccination has started on 20 Jun 2016 in Pcinja and Jablanica (Jablanicki) districts and it is foreseen in Kosovo, which has, reportedly, been infected as well (see 20160701.4321118). This may establish a buffer zone along the borders with FYR Macedonia and Albania. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4321622,79.]
